wiki.text:
'Englewood' is a corruption of Dutch Engelse buurt, or "English neighborhood",
which originally referred to Englewood, New Jersey's status as one of the few
English-speaking settlements in Dutch-speaking New Netherland. Today, the name
may refer to:
